We exalt you and declare you holy,/PR
according to the mystery of the murmurings/PR
of the holy seraphim,/PR
who declare the holiness of your Name,/PR
as it is written by your prophets./PR
"And each celestial being calls to another and exclaims:/PR
Holy, holy, holy is /SCT/XXHE /XXC/XXREATOR/XX of the Multitudes of Heaven!/PR
All the world is filled with divine glory!"/PR
/PR
GodÚs glory fills the world,/PR
as the ministering angels ask, one to another,/PR
"What place could contain GodÚs holiness?"/PR
And they are answered with a blessing:/PR
"Blessed is the glory of /SCT/XXHE /XXO/XXMNIPRESENT/XX,/PR
wherever God may dwell!"/PR
/PR
And from GodÚs place, God mercifully turns/PR
bestowing graciousness upon the people/PR
who declare the oneness of the divine name/PR
evening and morning, each day continually,/PR
as twice a day they say, with love: "Shema!"/PR
"Listen, Israel: /SCT/XXHE /XXE/XXTERNAL/XX is our God,/PR
/SCT/XXHE /XXE/XXTERNAL /XXO/XXNE/XX alone!"/PI/PR
